We Can Create Inner Class In Following Ways
- Nested Inner Class
- Local Inner Class
- Anonymous inner Class
- Static inner class

Local Inner Class : we Can Define a Class Inside a Method That Class is called as LocalInner Class
> This class only visible and useful inside a method
> This kind of classes are local to the  Method
> If Inheriting a class is only useful inside a method then we define inner class

Anonymous Inner Class :
> A Class with No Name is called an anonymous Class
> General Usage of anonymous class if for providing implementation for Abstarct class And for interface without creating the class

Static Inner Class :
> Static InnerClass are the Member of outer Class
> You can create the object of inner out side of the outer class also because they are static
> Static InnerClass Canot access the non static member of Outer class




